Global Villages is a term used by [[Franz Nahrada]] to describe local, [[self-sustaining]] [[communities]] that are nevertheless globally connected and [[collaborating]].

Not to be confused with the term "Global Village" coined by Marshall McLuhan to express the sensation of proximity in an era of mass media and mass communication.

